"26:135:6" : {s: 26, a: 135, w: 6, r: "عظم", t: "عَظِيمٍۢ", l: "عَظِيم", lc: 120, tl: "ʿaẓīmin", lb: "প্রচন্ড",e: "Great", b: "মহা", i: "yang besar", f: 18, rm: "great, important, big, regard, honour, mighty, glorious, a man of moment, All-mighty, All-glorious, grievous, bounty/abounding, magnify/increase. azzama - to make great."},
"26:136:1" : {s: 26, a: 136, w: 1, r: "قول", t: "قَالُوا۟", l: "قَالَ", lc: 1618, tl: "qālū", lb: "কথা বলা",e: "They said", b: "তারা বলে", i: "mereka berkata", f: 250, rm: "to say/speak, to call, to be named, word/speech, utterance, a thing said, greeting, discourse, one who says/speaks. To inspire/transmit/relate/answer/think/profess, emit an opinion on, indicate a state or condition or circumstance. qailun - speaker, indicator."},
